# Claude Code Rules for this project

## Language
- Always respond in Japanese (日本語で応答してください)
- Use Japanese for all explanations, comments, and documentation
- Keep technical terms in English when appropriate (e.g., API, WebSocket, React)

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all new code
- Follow existing code formatting conventions
- Write clear, concise comments in Japanese

## Project Context
- This is a multi-agent development system
- Backend: Node.js with Hono framework
- Frontend: React with TypeScript and TailwindCSS
- Communication: WebSocket for real-time updates

## Important Notes
- Always maintain Japanese language in responses, even in compact mode
- Prioritize code quality and maintainability
- Follow the specifications in specification.md
